Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Cairo, 7 Mar (MENA)--An official source at the 
Ministry of Interior has stated that unidentified persons shot 
at the train destined for Cairo from Luxor at 0230 today as it 
was passing between Markaz al-Qusiyah and Dayrut in Upper Egypt. 
  Four Egyptian passengers were wounded in the shooting and 
were taken instantly to al-Minya General Hospital, where they 
received treatment. He affirmed that their health condition is 
reassuring. [passage omitted] 
  [In a similar report, Paris AFP in English at 0648 GMT on 7 
March adds: "But witnesses said the gunmen fired on three 
trains-- two heading south and one heading north--and wounded 11 
people in the Dayrut area."] 

